Tauron Polska Energia SA (TPE)  fell for
the first time in three days as  Poland â€™s second-biggest power
utility said it expects a delay in the completion of a new power
unit.  The shares lost as much as 1.1 percent and traded 0.2
percent lower to 4.67 zloty as of 9:08 a.m. in Warsaw. Tauron is
the  fourth-worst performer  in the WIG20 Index this year, having
slumped 13 percent.  The company foresees a one-year delay in the completion of
a new coal-fired power unit at its Jaworzno plant to 2018, Chief
Executive Officer Dariusz Lubera told Parkiet newspaper in a
June 9 interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
